I played tons of Tetris on the Game Boy during those tedious road trips to visit the relatives.  I was so bad I'd fall asleep and see the little blocks.  *blushes*<br>
Final Fantasy VII was amazing.  The storyline, graphics, character development, and summoned creatures were all just wonderful.  I watched my boyfriend and his roomie play it for days before I just had to give it a go.<br>
Eternal Champions for Sega was a really nifty fighting game.  I know people will probably argue that there are better out there, but I actually liked this one.  For some reason the controls for this particular fighting game worked better for me than any others have so far.<br>
The James Bond Goldeneye(?)  4-player for Nintendo 64.  I had a great time getting whupped on by my boyfriend and a few of his buddies playing this one.<br>
