<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dune II</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
the mother of all RTS, for those of you that think that MS or Blizzard invented it. Amazing game for the time, the graphic detail was unbeleivable at a 320 x 240 screen with 256 colors.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Starcraft</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the finest RTS game for PvP. If you crash in a desert island with a lan, a few friends, and have to pick a single game to play forever, it has to be Starcraft<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Pools of Radiance</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> first RPG that raptured me. Am I the only one that remembers PoR when I see &quot;LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...&quot;? Damn, those zones took five minutes to load from a floppy, but was worth the wait!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Smaug system</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
The mother of all RPG online gaming. This is where EQ comes from, a fusion between the old text MUDs based in Smaug, plus UO, plus the 3d graphics. Smaug derived many rules from D&amp;D, that's why you still can find lots of simillitudes between EQ and D&amp;D. Some of the commands in the game are still unchanged from Smaug...<br>
