More like Dance Dance Revolution.  Like DDR, you need to follow the music and push the right button or move the control stick the right direction in response to what's on the screen.  Boring, right?  It's fun when you play it with the maraca controller's!  The maracas are actual maracas that respond to how high you hold them and shake them.  So, you need to shake the maraca's in response to what's on the screen.  Sounds insane, but by far the most entertaining game I've played, even more fun at a gathering of friends (or after the bars close....hehe, drunk samba <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <br>
<br>
It's a great game to play with friends, just too bad it's no longer available unless sega releases something similar on another system.  Though I doubt they will, because not many people bought the maracas, and without those, the games just not that great. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oligith>Oligith</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/lsteim/untitled.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf of Many Faces</span><br>  Posts: 641<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/23/03 9:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1588.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Most bestest fantabulistic video game(s) ever?</span><hr size=1> I still keep trying to get my old copy of Starcontrol II to work in windows XP.  I loved that game.<br>
